

{ Karl Marx

  1867 publizierte Karl Marx *Das Kapital*. Er sandte ein Exemplar des Buches an Darwin mit der Widmung *To Charles Darwin from a devoted admirer, Karl Marx, 1873*. 

  Darwin bedankte sich darauf mit einem Brief:
  "
    Dear Sir:

    I thank you for the honour which you have done me by sending me
    your great work on Capital; & I heartily wish that I
    was more worthy to receive it, by understanding more of the deep
    and important subject of political Economy. Though our studies
    have been so different, I belive that we both earnestly desire the
    extension Of Knowledge, & that this is in the long run sure to add to the
    happiness of Mankind.

    I remain, Dear Sir
    -
    Yours faithfully,

    Charles Darwin

  "

}

